item.title: Xi Jinping Scrutinizes Chinese Financial Institutions' Ties With Private Firms
item.description: Inspections of state banks and others are aimed at ensuring full Communist Party control over what is seen as the lifeblood of the economy, say people familiar with the plan.

item.title: In Poland, Protesters Fear Court Ruling Points to EU Exit
item.description: The fight between Warsaw and Brussels over laws, courts and money deepens following a Polish decision that overrules European Union authority.

item.title: Strange Quiet Arrives in Afghanistan After Decades of War
item.description: In the part of the country that saw the heaviest fighting, airstrikes have ceased and improvised mines have been defused. Residents are returning to the Taliban-controlled regions after years of displacement.

item.title: India, China Strike Out in Talks to Ease Border Dispute
item.description: Army commanders failed to reach a deal to defuse tensions along the neighborsâ€™ disputed border, as troop deployments in the region have reached their highest level in decades.

item.title: Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 Vaccine Is World's Preferred Shot
item.description: Countries from Latin America to the Middle East have lined up for the shot, driven by its effectiveness and ample supply, especially compared with Chinese and Russian rivals.

item.title: Afghan Interpreter Who Helped Rescue Biden in 2008 Escapes Afghanistan
item.description: After a personal plea to U.S. president, weeks in hiding and a clandestine evacuation, Aman Khalili and his family crossed the border into Pakistan.
